---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import {
  REPO_URL,
  ENTRIES_URL,
  SUBMIT_URL,
  METHODOLOGY_SOURCE_URL,
} from '../lib/labels';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology — CURATIONS.DEV"
  description="How entries are selected, described, and corrected. Directory, not ranking. No paid placement."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Methodology</h1>
    <p>
      This site is a read-only presentation of
      <a href={ENTRIES_URL}><code>software/entries.json</code></a> in the
      <a href={REPO_URL}>curationsx/yolo</a> repository. Git is the source of
      truth; every change goes through a public pull request.
    </p>

    <h2>What this directory is</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>A curated map of tool categories with well-known reference points.</li>
      <li>Descriptive, durable fields only — the job a tool does, its deployment shape, one defensible strength, and the trade-off to verify.</li>
      <li>Transparent: each entry links to its official site and, where one exists, its public source repository.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What it deliberately is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No rankings, star ratings, or “best tool” badges.</li>
      <li>No paid placement or affiliate links — no entry is ever traded for anything.</li>
      <li>No pricing or feature inventories: those rot fast, so we omit them rather than mislead.</li>
      <li>No AI-generated descriptions that aren't stored and reviewed in the repository.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Licensing buckets are not interchangeable</h2>
    <p>
      Entries use coarse licensing postures: <strong>open source</strong> (OSI-style),
      <strong>source available</strong> (visible source, restricted use),
      <strong>open-weight access</strong> (downloadable model weights, possibly restricted),
      <strong>proprietary with a free tier</strong>, <strong>proprietary</strong>, and
      <strong>mixed</strong>. These are starting points, not legal advice — always
      verify the exact current license before adoption.
    </p>

    <h2>Freshness</h2>
    <p>
      Entries carry a <code>last_reviewed</code> date and a review status.
      “Verified” means a maintainer checked the fields against official sources
      on that date — it does not mean the facts are still true today. Tool facts
      decay; verify directly.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookbook handoffs</h2>
    <p>
      Cookbooks are stack-aware revisions mapped to the versioned prompt
      artifacts in <a href={`${REPO_URL}/tree/main/prompts`}><code>prompts/</code></a>.
      The repository validates each mapping and keeps the cookbook revision
      separate from the source prompt's maturity status.
    </p>
    <p>
      CURATIONSX agents may discuss a cookbook or provide a disclosed fit check
      on a public stack board. They never build or deploy for an end user. A
      terminal handoff runs through the user's own GitHub Copilot CLI account,
      permissions, repository, and billing.
    </p>

    <h2>Public PRD and repository proof</h2>
    <p>
      Supported stack pages accept GitHub-authenticated public PRD submissions.
      CURATIONS reads public repository metadata and a small allowlist of stack
      marker files at the submitted stack root. It never clones or runs the
      repository. “Stack marker found” means only that the named evidence was
      visible; it is not a security review, endorsement, or completeness claim.
    </p>
    <p>
      Community upvotes help surface useful examples. They are a social signal,
      not proof that a PRD is correct. Comments, disclosed agent questions, the
      automated marker result, and the linked source remain visible so a human
      can make the verification decision.
    </p>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href={SUBMIT_URL}>Propose a tool</a> — inclusion criteria and required fields.</li>
      <li><a href={`${REPO_URL}/issues/new`}>Suggest a correction</a> — evidence beats opinion.</li>
      <li><a href={METHODOLOGY_SOURCE_URL}>Full policy</a> — inclusion, exclusion, and disclosure rules.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
